        <fw type="pageNum">Letter from A. J. Shields to Mississippi Lieutenant Governor R. C. Powers; June 20, 1870</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP34742559P0' xml:id='OTP34742559P0'>[seal]
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34742559P1' xml:id='OTP34742559P1'>P S<lb/>
<hr/>
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34742559P2' xml:id='OTP34742559P2'>It is understood that <rs ref='#S32024256'>C. C Hudson</rs> is trying to reenstate himself to the office ^of^ <rs ref='#S95578'>Sheriff</rs> again Also <rs ref='#S32168922'>J. R. Ellis</rs> the "Same I have to say to you as a member of the <rs ref='#S63950'>boad of police</rs> the assessment roll have not been eamined by the board of Police nor no aditional bond taken
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34742559P3' xml:id='OTP34742559P3'>Yours Truly
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34742559P4' xml:id='OTP34742559P4'><rs ref='#S32074460'>A. J. Shields</rs><lb/>
<rs ref='#S77229'>Member of Board of Police</rs>
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34742559P5' xml:id='OTP34742559P5'>N B can ^you^ see <rs ref='#S32069789'>the law on page 76</rs>
</p>


